1
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:18,599
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:18,599 --> 00:01:23,600
<i>[Episode 3]</i>

3
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:28,660
In the evening,

4
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:31,669
especially around the hour of hai (9 p.m. to 11 p.m.),

5
00:01:31,670 --> 00:01:34,189
drinking a moderate amount of black tea

6
00:01:34,189 --> 00:01:37,369
- can promote gastrointestinal motility.
- Na Na!

7
00:01:37,369 --> 00:01:38,930
Mr. Ma.

8
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:41,389
I brought supper over for you.

9
00:01:41,390 --> 00:01:42,890
Thanks.

10
00:01:43,730 --> 00:01:46,329
Where's the new tenant? Invite her down for food.

11
00:01:46,329 --> 00:01:48,600
She's not back yet.

12
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:51,339
It's already so late in the night.

13
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:52,389
Where could she possibly be?

14
00:01:52,390 --> 00:01:54,600
Maybe she's taking a stroll at the beach.

15
00:01:56,470 --> 00:01:58,499
The light in Damai's room is still on.

16
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,580
Call her down to eat.

17
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:03,249
Don't bother her. She's writing.

18
00:02:03,249 --> 00:02:05,969
She can decide whether to join us or not,

19
00:02:05,969 --> 00:02:08,269
but we're in the wrong if we don't invite her.

20
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:09,799
She doesn't like to be in a crowd.

21
00:02:09,799 --> 00:02:11,349
Stop pressuring others.

22
00:02:11,349 --> 00:02:14,579
Why am I in the wrong for being hospitable?

23
00:02:14,579 --> 00:02:16,269
She shouldn't stay cooped up in her room forever.

24
00:02:16,270 --> 00:02:19,339
She'll fall sick if she doesn't come out for fresh air.

25
00:02:19,339 --> 00:02:21,059
- Damai, come down for supper!
- Stop yelling!

26
00:02:21,059 --> 00:02:22,580
I'm sorry!

27
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:26,150
What did Damai say?

28
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:28,190
How do you know it's Damai?

29
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:33,610
Here, Mr. Ma.

30
00:02:33,610 --> 00:02:36,180
No food after noontime.

31
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:38,600
It's really her.

32
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:41,689
"I'm good." "Thank you."

33
00:02:41,689 --> 00:02:43,740
Good guess, Na Na.

34
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,619
All right. Have a drink.

35
00:02:46,619 --> 00:02:47,509
I won't drink.

36
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:51,609
I have to help out at the warehouse with Sister Xiaochun early tomorrow morning.

37
00:02:51,609 --> 00:02:55,590
What's with both of you? No food after noontime and no drinks after noontime.

38
00:02:55,620 --> 00:02:57,270
You guys are really...

39
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,230
I'll invite a friend over.

40
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:07,260
All of you are here!

41
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:09,229
Speak of the devil!

42
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,750
Come on, Chairman Xie. Have a drink.

43
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:12,109
You should've told me earlier.

44
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:14,740
We came back from dinner at my house.

45
00:03:15,270 --> 00:03:16,899
Who's this?

46
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,690
I'm Xu Hongdou, the new tenant.

47
00:03:19,690 --> 00:03:20,739
I live upstairs.

48
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:22,250
Nice to meet you. I'll introduce myself.

49
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,559
I'm Hu Youyu. Just call me Old Hu.

50
00:03:24,559 --> 00:03:26,580
- Nice to meet you, Old Hu.
- Nice to meet you, too.

51
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:29,800
This is Ma Qiushan. We call him Mr. Ma.

52
00:03:31,270 --> 00:03:33,620
I saw him meditating over there this afternoon.

53
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:35,190
- This is...
- Na Na.

54
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:37,140
Hello, Na Na.

55
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:39,550
So, a beautiful lady had dinner at your house?

56
00:03:39,550 --> 00:03:42,000
Aunty Baoping brought some beef over.

57
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,509
Why didn't you invite me over for beef?

58
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:45,970
If you guys came over, there won't be enough.

59
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:49,130
Well...You guys can drink. I'm busy tonight.

60
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:50,439
- Rest early.
- Okay.

61
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,709
How can you be busy at night? Have a drink!

62
00:03:52,709 --> 00:03:55,269
I'll take a rain check. I'm off!

63
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:59,689
Well, Hongdou, let's celebrate your arrival.

64
00:03:59,689 --> 00:04:02,419
I haven't unpacked yet.

65
00:04:02,419 --> 00:04:05,349
I need to tidy up first. We can do this tomorrow.

66
00:04:05,349 --> 00:04:06,419
Get an early rest.

67
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:09,049
Look for me if you need anything. I'm in this room.

68
00:04:09,049 --> 00:04:10,110
Okay.

69
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:13,740
Hongdou, shall we add each other on WeChat?

70
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,029
See, my phone is broken.

71
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,740
Let's wait until it's fixed.

72
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,479
- Good night.
- Good night.

73
00:04:19,479 --> 00:04:20,939
I... I live in that room.

74
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:22,780
If you have any difficulties, you can look for me, too.

75
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:24,350
<i>Okay.</i>

76
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:29,460
All right.

77
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:31,300
She's also introverted.

78
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:33,840
Even more introverted than Damai.

79
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,349
I'll head back first.

80
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:37,399
Thanks for your supper.

81
00:04:37,399 --> 00:04:39,220
Hey, stay a little longer.

82
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:42,710
Wait... At least leave me some barbecue.

83
00:04:42,710 --> 00:04:44,960
Old Hu.

84
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:47,250
Let it be.

85
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:50,260
People should learn

86
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:54,420
to be comfortable with themselves.

87
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:57,590
Let's meditate.

88
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:02,230
I'll drink on my own.

89
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:38,440
♫ <i>Listen to the rain falling into the silent forest</i> ♫

90
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:45,500
♫ <i>Enjoy the mountainous landscape at sunset</i> ♫

91
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,909
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

92
00:05:50,910 --> 00:05:53,240
<i>We can eat now, right?</i>

93
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,980
<i>Let's dig in.</i>

94
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:56,670
<i>Wait.</i>

95
00:05:57,550 --> 00:06:01,460
<i>I have to introduce these three dishes to you.</i>

96
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:02,950
<i>Mother and Son Reunion.</i>

97
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:05,320
<i>Battle of Guan Yu and Qing Qiong.</i>

98
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,270
<i>Spicy Kiss.</i>

99
00:06:07,270 --> 00:06:09,160
<i>Aren't these stir-fried soybean sprouts with mung bean sprouts,</i>

100
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:11,249
<i>tomato omelette, and fried pig snouts with chili?</i>

101
00:06:11,249 --> 00:06:12,739
<i>Don't you find these dishes interesting?</i>

102
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:15,510
<i>I just think this restaurant serves food too slowly.</i>

103
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:17,899
<i>Here's the thing. I have to head back to the hotel right after dinner.</i>

104
00:06:17,899 --> 00:06:20,050
<i>A tour group arrived today.</i>

105
00:06:20,050 --> 00:06:22,050
<i>Don't you think I‘ve lost my mind?</i>

106
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:23,909
<i>I'm so busy that I even have ulcers in my mouth,</i>

107
00:06:23,910 --> 00:06:26,219
<i>but I'm still joining you for fried pig snouts with chili.</i>

108
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:29,079
<i>Fine, I get it. That's because you love me.</i>

109
00:06:29,079 --> 00:06:30,950
<i>You're becoming too much to love.</i>

110
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:32,109
<i>- Waiter!
- Yeah!</i>

111
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:33,709
<i>A bowl of rice, please! Hurry up!</i>

112
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:34,810
<i>Okay. Please wait a moment.</i>

113
00:06:34,810 --> 00:06:37,690
<i>When will you finally be free to travel to Yunnan with me?</i>

114
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:39,840
<i>I'm busy lately.</i>

115
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,590
<i>We'll see.</i>

116
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:45,429
<i>Actually, I just want to try their water poplar flower soup.</i>

117
00:06:45,429 --> 00:06:47,199
<i>Water poplar flower soup?</i>

118
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:49,490
<i>How did it get this name?</i>

119
00:06:49,490 --> 00:06:51,819
<i>That vegetable is called water poplar flower.</i>

120
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,379
<i>I don't know. I've never tasted it either. </i>

121
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:56,050
<i>It probably tastes like vegetable soup.</i>

122
00:06:56,050 --> 00:07:00,340
♫ <i>When the wind rises, the sky will be cloudless</i> ♫

123
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:03,229
<i>The fried pig snout tastes amazing.</i>

124
00:07:03,230 --> 00:07:04,859
<i>- You should eat more.
- Hey!</i>

125
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:07,789
<i>Please refer to it as "Spicy Kiss."</i>

126
00:07:07,790 --> 00:07:09,539
<i>Fried pig snout.</i>
- <i>Tour group.</i>

127
00:07:09,539 --> 00:07:10,930
<i>- Fried pig snout.
- Tour group. Tour group. Tour group.</i>

128
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:13,200
<i>Fried pig snout. Fried pig snout.</i>

129
00:07:15,110 --> 00:07:17,110
Yum.

130
00:07:17,110 --> 00:07:18,680
So yummy.

131
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:25,970
♫ <i>I'll head to a windy place to meet you</i> ♫

132
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,540
Kitty!

133
00:08:42,590 --> 00:08:44,050
Hi!

134
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:47,620
Hi.

135
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:50,140
My name is Xu Hongdou. What's yours?

136
00:08:51,310 --> 00:08:52,539
I didn't sleep well yesterday.

137
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:55,370
The window was open and mosquitoes were coming in.

138
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,610
Let me pet you.

139
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,640
Hi, nice to meet you.

140
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:33,589
I'm Xu Hongdou. I arrived yesterday.

141
00:09:33,589 --> 00:09:35,620
Hello, my name is Damai.

142
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:37,069
Damai.

143
00:09:37,070 --> 00:09:39,019
Hongdou and Damai.

144
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:40,790
We're both food.
<i>(T/N: Hongdou refers to red bean and Damai refers to barley)</i>

145
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:48,780
You're up so early.

146
00:09:48,780 --> 00:09:50,790
I haven't slept yet.

147
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,310
Did you stay up all night?

148
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:54,539
Well, I'm almost done with cooking.

149
00:09:54,539 --> 00:09:56,559
It's fine. I won't be eating.

150
00:09:56,559 --> 00:09:57,989
I'm just saying hello.

151
00:09:57,990 --> 00:09:59,840
Please go on.

152
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:06,199
I've cooked too much. Would you like to have some?

153
00:10:06,199 --> 00:10:07,739
No, thanks.

154
00:10:07,740 --> 00:10:10,829
I... I'll make myself a bowl of cereal later.

155
00:10:10,830 --> 00:10:11,850
Thank you.

156
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:14,660
It's no big deal. I've really made too much.

157
00:10:16,590 --> 00:10:19,359
All right then. Thank you.

158
00:10:29,780 --> 00:10:32,120
Who owns the cat?

159
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,720
I don't know.

160
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:46,890
- Are there mosquitoes in your room?
- Yeah.

161
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:48,689
I forgot to close the windows before heading to bed last night.

162
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:51,020
There are a lot of mosquitoes here.

163
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:54,619
I have insecticide and essential balm in my room.

164
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,160
I'll pass them to you later.

165
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,040
Sure. Thank you.

166
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:03,860
You sound like you have a Hunan accent.

167
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:07,499
I used to work in a hotel.

168
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,739
A well-acquainted VIP customer of mine

169
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:12,120
was also from Hunan Province.

170
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,110
Your accents are similar.

171
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,540
Where is the hotel?

172
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:25,259
A five-star hotel in Beijing.

173
00:11:25,260 --> 00:11:27,910
So, you're from Beijing?

174
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,820
Nope.

175
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:32,229
I studied in Beijing.

176
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:35,690
Then, I found a job in Beijing.

177
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:38,090
I spent more than ten years in Beijing.

178
00:11:38,090 --> 00:11:39,990
I am from Shandong Province.

179
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,200
Well, why are you here?

180
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:52,900
I quit my job. I came here to relax and unwind.

181
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,700
How are you going to do that?

182
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,200
Have you just changed a spot to scroll through your phone?

183
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:07,100
That's not it. The scenery here is gorgeous.

184
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:09,800
It's worthwhile to try putting away my phone.

185
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:12,259
So, what are your plans for today?

186
00:12:12,259 --> 00:12:16,400
Fixing my phone. My phone is broken.

187
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,300
Isn't it the perfect chance to go offline?

188
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:22,000
As long as your phone is within reach, you'll always want to use it.

189
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,600
Now that it isn't working, you won't want to use it.

190
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:27,600
Well...

191
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,600
Since I cooked breakfast, can you wash the dishes?

192
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,900
Of course. You can rest.

193
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:37,600
Thank you.

194
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,100
Then, I'm off.

195
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:01,420
<i>[Got you a book to pass the time.]</i>

196
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:32,899
Breakfast!

197
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:35,100
Hurry up! I'm about to be late for work.

198
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:36,160
Got it. All right.

199
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:38,609
Granny can't wait.

200
00:14:38,609 --> 00:14:41,230
She's angry.

201
00:14:41,230 --> 00:14:43,190
Let's have breakfast.

202
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:45,659
Our young master hasn't come down yet.

203
00:14:45,659 --> 00:14:47,789
What's up with him? Does he want to be served breakfast in bed?

204
00:14:47,789 --> 00:14:49,949
Xiao Hu Lu, get your uncle down for breakfast.

205
00:14:49,949 --> 00:14:51,650
Go on.

206
00:14:51,650 --> 00:14:53,189
Don't be angry with him.

207
00:14:53,190 --> 00:14:55,189
His heart is long gone.

208
00:14:55,190 --> 00:14:57,580
He won't listen to us anymore.

209
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,340
Yeah, he won't.

210
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:01,070
No matter what I tell him,

211
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:04,609
it goes in one ear and out the other. Nothing enters his brain.

212
00:15:04,609 --> 00:15:07,930
If I were angry with him, he would've pissed me off into my grave by now.

213
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:10,509
Don't let anger kill you. A single casualty like me is enough.

214
00:15:10,509 --> 00:15:13,080
Your dad is waiting for me in the afterlife anyway.

215
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,320
Li Baoping!

216
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,359
You are the last person who should be killed by anger.

217
00:15:17,359 --> 00:15:18,619
You've suffered terribly in life.

218
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,189
Now, it's finally time for you to enjoy retirement.

219
00:15:20,190 --> 00:15:23,360
If you die of anger, even the King of Hell won't approve.

220
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:25,640
The ghosts won't dare to claim your soul.

221
00:15:26,970 --> 00:15:28,859
Let Dad wait a few more years.

222
00:15:28,859 --> 00:15:30,930
He can wait several decades.

223
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:34,859
Granny, Uncle won't get up.

224
00:15:34,860 --> 00:15:37,920
Uncle A'Yuan is also sleeping in his room.

225
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,830
Okay, you can eat breakfast.

226
00:15:40,470 --> 00:15:42,139
When did A'Yuan come over?

227
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:43,890
I don't know.

228
00:15:44,470 --> 00:15:46,190
I'll go upstairs and have a look.

229
00:16:28,350 --> 00:16:30,470
Are you the new tenant?

230
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:32,549
Yes. Hello.

231
00:16:32,549 --> 00:16:34,539
Hello and welcome.

232
00:16:34,540 --> 00:16:35,899
Mr. Ma.

233
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:36,949
You don't have to greet him.

234
00:16:36,950 --> 00:16:39,800
He can't hear you during the day.

235
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,910
Newbie.

236
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:45,250
I need to make some things clear to you.

237
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:48,139
I'm responsible for cleaning this yard.

238
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:51,659
Don't throw your garbage haphazardly or leave it at your door.

239
00:16:51,660 --> 00:16:54,269
Leave it in the garbage bin next to the laundry room.

240
00:16:54,269 --> 00:16:56,209
Can you see it? Your garbage goes there.

241
00:16:56,209 --> 00:16:59,259
One more thing, you have to clean your room yourself.

242
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:00,389
I won't be responsible for that.

243
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:01,270
- Okay.
- Got it?

244
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:03,449
Yes. I got it.

245
00:17:04,150 --> 00:17:06,180
You're very pretty.

246
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:08,710
Just like my girl, Xiao Xi.

247
00:17:08,710 --> 00:17:10,960
Why did you come here?

248
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,909
I'm here to take a break.

249
00:17:12,910 --> 00:17:14,470
The air here is fresh.

250
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:15,909
What about your job?

251
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:17,570
I quit.

252
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:22,859
Only city folks like you are bold enough to quit your job as you please.

253
00:17:22,859 --> 00:17:25,770
I'm not an employee.

254
00:17:25,770 --> 00:17:29,059
One-third of the rooms in this courtyard belong to me.

255
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:30,650
I'm a landlady.

256
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:32,149
Oh, Mrs. Landlady!

257
00:17:32,150 --> 00:17:35,500
No wonder you have such a dignified tone.

258
